 chosen from the dead. After leaving the shelter of the undead, go on a journey to the lands of the ancient lords. Hit the bell of awakening, and you will discover the fate of the undead.\r\n\r\nBut in the kingdom everything was not at all rosy and without taking into account the approaching darkness - Gwyn and the other gods nearly fell victim to the conspiracy. Unknown cultists have created a dark coal, with which you can forge weapons that can even destroy God. The leader of the conspirators was Havel Scala, a close friend of Gwyn and a bishop of the White Way, a covenant that destroyed the damned dead and was looking for new ways to kindle a flame. The plan was uncovered, and Havel went to eternal imprisonment, and Gwin lost his valuable ally.\r\n\r\nLooking at the confusion, many gods simply left Anor Londo and disappeared into the far lands. Among them was Guenever, who fled with the god of fire Flannom. These upheavals left their mark on Gwyn: he became suspicious and imprisoned the goddess of sin Velka, fearing that he himself could be included in the list of sinners. Her prison was the painted world of Ariamis, a place created to hide especially unpleasant secrets.\r\n\r\nBut most of all Gwin was shocked by the incident in Isalit\r\n\r\n.<img class=\" wp-image-151 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/7b6b23af5235bd74-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"357\" height=\"201\" />\r\n\r\nThe witch Isalita, long considering how to maintain a fading flame, eventually decided to create a new one with the help of fiery magic.\r\n\r\nTo some extent, she succeeded, but her fire turned ugly and defiled, swallowed the witch herself and spawned a bed of chaos that gave rise to disgusting demons. The inhabitants of the city perished one by one, and a few survivors mutated into horrible creatures. Even the children of the witch did not escape the terrible fate: the son turned into a huge formless demon, and two daughters partially lost their human appearance.\r\n\r\nGwyn sent to fight with demons his best knights. Most of them fell in battle, and those that survived, impoverished their armor in a demonic flame and dark shadows are still chasing chaos creatures all over Lord Lord.\r\n\r\nGwin was left with nothing. The family left him. His powers are scattered throughout the world. The remaining companions can be counted on the fingers. The fire was almost extinguished.\r\n\r\nThen the king made a fateful decision: to go into the crucible of the original flame and sacrifice himself in a desperate attempt to kindle a fire. From the monarch there was only an empty shell, he burned to the ground and became the first lord of the ashes. But the only great soul was not enough. The victim of Gwyn helped extend the era of fire for a moment, but Lorddrain was emptied, and the curse of the undead was never defeated.\r\n\r\nHowever, hope has not completely died out. In Lordrand still there was a god - Gvindolin. Gwyn\'s son remained waiting for the chosen dead man, the one who can get great souls and with their help to kindle the first flame.\r\n\r\nThe chosen dead man did come. The same warrior who once struck Manus of the Abyssal Father, glided through the lands of Lorddran with a grim reaper and pulled out the great souls from the hands of the former gods. Four kings, a bed of chaos, Nito, Nagy Sith - all fell from his hand.\r\n\r\nDid he use his power to prolong the era of fire? Some say that yes, preferring to believe in fairy tales. The chosen dead man nobly sacrificed himself, burned and made the flame shine as brightly as at the moment of birth.\r\n\r\nBut in reality there is no place for such nobility.','Analysis of the plot, part 3','','publish','open','open','','analysis-of-the-plot-part-3','','','2018-04-22 02:02:18','2018-04-21 23:02:18','',0,'http://localhost:8000/?p=187',0,'post','',0),(188,1,'2018-04-22 02:02:18','2018-04-21 23:02:18','The insidious serpent again manifested itself in New Londo, a great 