something incredibly valuable. Nobody knows for sure what exactly the king brought from across the sea, but thanks to this thing, he comprehended the mystery of the creation of golems - artificial creatures, animated with the help of souls. With their help, impregnable walls were erected, huge bridges were built and Dranglik Castle was rebuilt.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-154 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/83c893438db702c6-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"382\" height=\"215\" />\r\n\r\nIn the kingdom of Vendric the world reigned. Until the first carriers of the sign of darkness appeared. The flame began to fade.\r\n\r\nThe damned dead grew bigger and the king did not know how to fight it. Undead tried to destroy, lock in cages, take away on ships to distant lands, but the bearers of the sign became more and more. Vendric was frightened, because he was also a man and was afraid of \"catching\" a curse from his subjects.\r\n\r\nThen he turned to his brother, hoping to find a cure with him.\r\n\r\nIn search of answers, the brothers decided to turn to the dragons, but not to their weak descendants, who did not have a little power of their ancestors, but to ancient primordial creatures. And the truth is, who else can reveal the secrets of life and death, if not the ones that never lived and died?\r\n\r\nIt remains a mystery where Aldia could have known about the nature of the first dragons, but with the help of the bones of the ancient dragon and the soul of one of the giants, a creature was created - a copy of the former masters of the world. And it began to speak.\r\n\r\nNobody knows what exactly Vendric and Aldia managed to find out from the twin of the ancient dragon, but soon after its creation Shanalotta appeared, she is the Emerald Messenger, a dragon child, brought up by people. Later, it was sometimes described as the last keeper of fire, and this fairly accurately conveys the meaning of its purpose. Apparently, the dragon had revealed to the king and his brother the true cause of the curse, and they conceived the idea of ​​creating a creature capable of forever sustaining the original flame. But their plan failed, Shanalotta turned out not the way they expected, and the curse with her help could not be defeated.\r\n<div class=\"awim_wideimg\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://cdn.igromania.ru/mnt/articles/2/9/e/7/1/9/27776/html/img/d5746d659bedb520.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"647\" height=\"309\" border=\"0\" />\r\n<div>► In spite of everything, Shanalotta tried to somehow fulfill her destiny and later directed the damned dead in the hope that among them there would be someone who could kindle a flame.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>A dark soul</h1>\r\nCrushing melancholy, forgotten joy, a sense of obsession with a lost thing and a sincere hope to regain it ... Could these thoughts belong to a monster from the abyss? But, maybe, if so, it was not a monster?\r\n\r\nHowever, the curse was the less of the problems of the kingdom - the giants came to take their. A long, bloody war broke out, affecting several generations at once.\r\n\r\nVendric had a hard time, Dranglik lay in ruins. The war marked a turning point: Vendric first seriously thought about the source of his misfortunes. Giants took revenge on Dranglick for the invasion, but were they really going to attack the kingdom first? Who persuaded the king to invade other lands and steal the sacred artifact? Vandrik realized that the darkness was getting closer to him than he could have expected, and her name was Nasandra. But who was his queen, and what was the threat from her?\r\n\r\nThis Vendrik could not know. Maybe it\'s for the best.\r\n\r\nMany centuries ago, when the first man Manus was struck in the abyss, his soul was divided into parts. Each of these pieces reflected the sides of the personality of the Abyssal Father, and each took shape.\r\n\r\nThe first was Elana, a reflection of the rage and malice of Manus. She became a companion of the Drowning King, who long ago ruled the beautiful underground city of Shulva, whose inhabitants worshiped the living ancient dragon Sina. Elana used the king to be closer to the slumbering dragon. She fed on his power and saved her soul in the hope of sooner or later strike and avenge her \"father.\"','Analyze the plot of Dark Souls: the era of darkness, part 1','','publish','open','open','','analyze-the-plot-of-dark-souls-the-era-of-darkness-part-1','','','2018-04-22 02:06:31','2018-04-21 23:06:31','',0,'http://localhost:8000/?p=189',0,'post','',0),(190,1,'2018-04-22 02:06:31','2018-04-21 23:06:31','More information about what happened in the first Dark Souls, you can read in the first part - here.\r\n\r\nAnyone who believes that there is no plot in Dark Souls is dedicated.\r\n\r\nIt is not known how many years have passed since the reign of Gwyn and as soon as the flames flickered again, but where Lordrand once was, many kingdoms were born, see their flowering and mouth.\r\n\r\nAnd then came the brothers Vendrik and Aldia. Vendric killed four unnamed greats and got their souls. The power gained enabled him to found the great kingdom of Dranglik. No one knows exactly how the king ordered the souls, but he himself was a man, and his kingdom was built for people. It is rumored that he sacrificed his soul to the first flame, thanks to which he was able to find a human face together with his future subjects.\r\n<h1>A new dawn</h1>\r\nThere are only two ways: follow the rules of this world or destroy them.\r\n\r\nEvery king needs a loyal queen, is not it? Wendrick\'s wife came from distant lands and warned the king of the threat from giants living overseas and ready to destroy the young kingdom.\r\n\r\nGathering his best warriors, Vendric went on a campaign, plundered the lands of giants and stole from them something incredibly valuable. Nobody knows for sure what exactly the king brought from across the sea, but thanks to this thing, he comprehended the mystery of the crea