e. But their plan failed, Shanalotta turned out not the way they expected, and the curse with her help could not be defeated.\r\n<div class=\"awim_wideimg\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://cdn.igromania.ru/mnt/articles/2/9/e/7/1/9/27776/html/img/d5746d659bedb520.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"647\" height=\"309\" border=\"0\" />\r\n<div>► In spite of everything, Shanalotta tried to somehow fulfill her destiny and later directed the damned dead in the hope that among them there would be someone who could kindle a flame.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>A dark soul</h1>\r\nCrushing melancholy, forgotten joy, a sense of obsession with a lost thing and a sincere hope to regain it ... Could these thoughts belong to a monster from the abyss? But, maybe, if so, it was not a monster?\r\n\r\nHowever, the curse was the less of the problems of the kingdom - the giants came to take their. A long, bloody war broke out, affecting several generations at once.\r\n\r\nVendric had a hard time, Dranglik lay in ruins. The war marked a turning point: Vendric first seriously thought about the source of his misfortunes. Giants took revenge on Dranglick for the invasion, but were they really going to attack the kingdom first? Who persuaded the king to invade other lands and steal the sacred artifact? Vandrik realized that the darkness was getting closer to him than he could have expected, and her name was Nasandra. But who was his queen, and what was the threat from her?\r\n\r\nThis Vendrik could not know. Maybe it\'s for the best.\r\n\r\nMany centuries ago, when the first man Manus was struck in the abyss, his soul was divided into parts. Each of these pieces reflected the sides of the personality of the Abyssal Father, and each took shape.\r\n\r\nThe first was Elana, a reflection of the rage and malice of Manus. She became a companion of the Drowning King, who long ago ruled the beautiful underground city of Shulva, whose inhabitants worshiped the living ancient dragon Sina. Elana used the king to be closer to the slumbering dragon. She fed on his power and saved her soul in the hope of sooner or later strike and avenge her \"father.\"','Analyze the plot of Dark Souls: the era of darkness, part 1','','inherit','closed','closed','','189-revision-v1','','','2018-04-22 02:06:31','2018-04-21 23:06:31','',189,'http://localhost:8000/189-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(191,1,'2018-04-22 02:09:17','2018-04-21 23:09:17','<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-157 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/b1ac53f5bf260f4c-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" />\r\n\r\nThe second was Nadalia, the embodiment of the loneliness of the Abyssal Father. Her intentions remain unknown, because when she came to the Iron King to become his wife, he already disappeared.\r\n\r\nThe old Iron King was a mighty ruler who managed to raise his kingdom from the very bottom. In his lands, a huge amount of iron was mined, forged and melted unprecedented armor, weapons and mechanisms.\r\n\r\nThe creations of the king were as great as they were terrible. He created a metal demon from a smelter, which received a real soul. The demon also ruined the king. In one blow, he sent the man into the red-hot lava, where the king met with something that also turned him into a huge ugly demon.\r\n\r\nIn desperation, Nadaliya renounced her body and settled in the hazy tower, behind a poisonous fog. Under his influence, people became unquestioning slaves to a lonely queen.\r\n<div class=\"awim_wideimg\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://cdn.igromania.ru/mnt/articles/2/9/e/7/1/9/27776/html/img/239145bf09407777.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"647\" height=\"907\" border=\"0\" />\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n► Before her death or until the end of time, Nadaliya will be alone in waiting for her king.\r\nThe third fragment of the soul of Manus became Alsanna, a mute oracle, always reassuring the awakened fire of chaos in the town of Eleum Lois. It is a symbol of hope, the only bright feeling that lived in the heart of the first person.\r\n\r\nShe became the wife of the King of ivory, with her guarding the subjects from the chaos. The king felt the dark beginning of Alsanna, but trusted her. Before going to the heart of the chaos to finish him off once and for all, he left Alsanna the highest symbol of power - the ceremonial blade of Eleus Lois.\r\n\r\nAlsanna overcame the darkness within herself: even after the death of the king, she remained in her eternal post.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"awim_wideimg\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://cdn.igromania.ru/mnt/articles/2/9/e/7/1/9/27776/html/img/163973c510a12412.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"647\" height=\"364\" border=\"0\" />\r\n<div>► Alsanna is a living confirmation that Manus was not always a monster.\r\nThe fourth fragment was embodied in Nashendra, the personification of the obsession with Manus. He was so eager to get a certain thing, that for her sake, at the risk of everyone, he dragged an elected dead man in his time. Nashandra also wanted the strength of the first flame. She manipulated Vendric with all the truths and crooks pushing him to burn the flame, sacrificing himself. After the death of the king, the force of the original fire would have gotten to her, and Manus, her father, would have been avenged.</div>\r\n</div>','The Epoch of Darkness, part 2','','publish','open','open','','the-epoch-of-darkness-part-2','','','2018-04-22 02:09:17','2018-04-21 23:09:17','',0,'http://localhost:8000/?p=191',0,'post','',0),(192,1,'2018-04-22 02:09:17','2018-04-21 23:09:17','<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-157 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/b1ac53f5bf260f4c-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" />\r\n\r\nThe second was Nadalia, the embodiment of the loneliness of the Abyssal Father. Her intentions remain unknown, because when she came to the Iron King to become his wife, he already disappeared.\r\n\r\nThe old Iron King was a mighty ruler who managed to raise his kingdom 