ndead and walled himself behind a door that only a man can open. With him, he took the royal ring, necessary for opening the gates to the throne of desires, standing in the crucible of the first flame. The king did everything to ensure that Nasandra never reached the throne. His only hope, as in Gwyn\'s time, was the appearance of a new elected dead man.\r\n<div class=\"awim_wideimg\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://cdn.igromania.ru/mnt/articles/2/9/e/7/1/9/27776/html/img/73edd88b4fbbcc3e.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"647\" height=\"377\" border=\"0\" />\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n► Vendric, with the help of Aldiah, wanted to move his soul into an artificial body to get rid of the curse, but Aldia disappeared without a trace, and later returned to a shapeless, repulsive being.\r\nAnd such a dead man was found again. Under the auspices of Shanalotta, he passed through the cursed lands of Dranglick. From his hand fell the lord of giants, who once turned Dranglik into ruins. And a forgotten sinner who sentenced herself to eternal suffering for an unsuccessful attempt to kindle a flame. And the old Iron King, who, according to rumors, found a piece of Gwyn\'s soul in the lava. Rotting in the depths of the garbage dump, adopted, as they say, the power of the first of the dead.\r\n\r\nAnd even the offspring of Manus did not escape the sword of the hero. Powerful souls nurtured a dead man, and he could sit on the throne of desire, extending the era of fire.\r\n\r\nBut the chosen dead man again chose a different path. He met Aldia, and he convinced him of the pointlessness of continuing the cycle. Burn a fire or give the world to darkness - it does not matter. The fire will return, and the curse of the undead will always accompany him. The cycle must be interrupted.\r\n\r\nVendrik wanted this, but he did not have the strength. Will there be enough for an elected dead man? Unlike Vendric, he was able to obtain the crowns of all the great kings. This did not remove the curse itself, but completely removed its symptoms. The hero was no longer afraid of becoming \"hollow\". He remained a man, no matter how much he died. He went beyond the cycle and went in search of funds from the curse, leaving the flame to slowly fade.\r\n\r\nFrom the final (if, of course, there is no unexpectedly-unexpected Dark Souls 4 - a joke!) Part of the cycle you will learn about the era of people.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','The Epoch of Darkness, part 3','','publish','open','open','','the-epoch-of-darkness-part-3','','','2018-04-22 02:12:04','2018-04-21 23:12:04','',0,'http://localhost:8000/?p=193',0,'post','',0),(194,1,'2018-04-22 02:12:04','2018-04-21 23:12:04','<h1>Eternal damnation</h1>\r\nThe throne will take you. But the question remains ... What do you really need? Shine? Dark? Or something completely different?\r\n\r\nSensing the threat in Nasandra, Vendrik abandoned the idea of ​​flaming fire at the cost of his own life. He was determined to find a way to break the cycle, to get out of the endless circle of fading and igniting the fire, while saving humanity from the curse.\r\n\r\nAfter much hesitation, he decided to get the crowns of other kings. How this was supposed to save the undead from the curse and who gave this idea to Vendrik is not known, but, most likely, his brother, Aldiya, was most likely behind it. Who knows what discoveries he made within the walls of his mansion? Yes, and Vendrik himself was famous as a man who knew the secrets of the soul. Perhaps, it was in the souls of the carriers of those crowns that it was the case?\r\n\r\nVendric sent his knights to Shulva, where they attacked the dragon Sina, but disappeared from the poison that had expired from his chest. In the hazy tower, all the knights died in the fight against the servants of Nadalya. In both cases, Vendric did not move one step closer to the crowns. Prior to Eleus Lois, his warriors probably did not make it at all.\r\n\r\nIn despair, Vendric went to the crypt of the undead and walled himself be