INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (195,1,'2018-04-22 02:15:03','2018-04-21 23:15:03','Exploring the north, the pilgrims are convinced that the old stories do not lie. The castle, which is called Lotrick, stands where the lands of the ascendants of the ashes converge. Where the great flame was once born and gas.\r\n\r\nAnd it goes out again. The bell rings, and the ascendants of the ashes rise from their graves. They will leave their thrones, and the ignorant will rise - the damned undead, unworthy to become ashes. Non-burning always looking for coals.\r\n<h1>The Dark Blessing</h1>\r\nWe, who are not burning, are miserable creatures. We can not even die. And they want us to seek the lords of the ashes and return them to the moldy thrones. It makes me angry. But we are the true legends, we have enough courage to light a fire. It is not good for us to grovel before them.\r\n\r\nNo one knows how many cycles of fading and firing the fire survived this world. And the flow of time here is twisted - different epochs converge in one place, and the heroes of the former times appear in the flesh, then disappear, as if they never existed. Centuries pass by; kingdoms on the lands of the Lordana grow, go and are forgotten.\r\n\r\nBut the outer lands are unchanged. Astor, Mirra, Vinheim - the local pilgrims still come here. But how is this possible? Perhaps, there, outside the Lordran, time moves in a straight line, but in the homeland of the first flame it slows down, then it accelerates its course, or even turns back altogether? Maybe one year in outer lands is equal to a hundred years spent on the land of ancient gods?\r\n\r\nHowever that may be, the kingdom of Guinea fell many centuries ago, and even no one remembers Dranglick. The bell rings, and the lords of the ashes awaken. In addition to them rebel and non-fouling, the same undead as all the damned, but something makes them special. When the original flame flares up with renewed vigor and its tongues glide along the earth - the damned burn. Their white bones become the foundation and fuel of the fires that carry the light of the flame to all corners of the world. They fulfill their destiny.\r\n\r\nBut there are those whom the flame rejects. They are only forgotten by a long sleep awaiting the blows of the bell. When the flame begins to fade, they will go to seek the lords to take their thrones. Those who do not have a soul - they are only vessels that can accommodate as many foreign souls as needed. Therefore, they can not become \"hollow\". They will die hundreds of times, but they will not lose their reason and will continue their search. The lords must sit on the thrones prepared for them in the temple of fire. Either they are their ashes.\r\n<div class=\"awim_wideimg\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://cdn.igromania.ru/mnt/articles/8/a/a/f/e/b/27783/html/img/13067ec2b14e1d62.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"647\" height=\"364\" border=\"0\" />\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n► Not all noncombatants are ready to fulfill their mission. Many reject debt and go roam the world, pursuing their own goals.\r\nBut where did the lords of the ashes come from? Aldrik, the patron saint of the depths, legion of the undead of Farron, the gloomy giant Jorm. How did they acquire the title that Gwyn himself wore?\r\n\r\nIt is said that each of them once burned a flame and that they must do it again. But few are ready to go. Guided by only their known goals, the lords leave their tombs. Non-burning people go hunting. But who are those who are declared to hunt?\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','The analysis of the plot of Dark Souls: the era of people','','publish','open','open','','the-analysis-of-the-plot-of-dark-souls-the-era-of-people','','','2018-04-22 02:15:03','2018-04-21 23:15:03','',0,'http://localhost:8000/?p=195',0,'post','',0),(196,1,'2018-04-22 02:15:03','2018-04-21 23:15:03','Exploring the north, the pilgrims are convinced that the old stories do not lie. The castle, which is called Lotrick, stands where the lands of the ascenda